name: $Address
desc: A duration of time during which an organism (or a process) has existed.

name: $Age
desc: A  text note which also  contains information about who made the statement and when.

name: $Annotation
desc: For referring to data content defined in other formats.

name: $Attachment
desc: Base definition for all elements that are defined inside a resource - but not those in a data type.

name: $BackboneElement
desc: A concept that may be defined by a formal reference to a terminology or ontology or may be provided by text.

name: $CodeableConcept
desc: A reference to a code defined by a terminology system.

name: $Coding
desc: Specifies contact information for a person or organization.

name: $ContactDetail
desc: Details for all kinds of technology mediated contact points for a person or organization, including telephone, email, etc.

name: $ContactPoint
desc: A contributor to the content of a knowledge asset, including authors, editors, reviewers, and endorsers.

name: $Contributor
desc: A measured amount (or an amount that can potentially be measured). Note that measured amounts include amounts that are not precisely quantified, including amounts involving arbitrary units and floating currencies.

name: $Count
desc: Describes a required data item for evaluation in terms of the type of data, and optional code or date-based filters of the data.

name: $DataRequirement
desc: A length - a value with a unit that is a physical distance.

name: $Distance
desc: Indicates how the medication is/was taken or should be taken by the patient.

name: $Dosage
desc: A length of time.

name: $Duration
desc: Base definition for all elements in a resource.

name: $Element
desc: Captures constraints on each element within the resource, profile, or extension.

name: $ElementDefinition
desc: Optional Extension Element - found in all resources.

name: $Extension
desc: A human's name with the ability to identify parts and usage.

name: $HumanName
desc: A technical identifier - identifies some entity uniquely and unambiguously.

name: $Identifier
desc: The metadata about a resource. This is content in the resource that is maintained by the infrastructure. Changes to the content may not always be associated with version changes to the resource.

name: $Meta
desc: An amount of economic utility in some recognized currency.

name: $Money
desc: A human-readable formatted text, including images.

name: $Narrative
desc: The parameters to the module. This collection specifies both the input and output parameters. Input parameters are provided by the caller as part of the $evaluate operation. Output parameters are included in the GuidanceResponse.

name: $ParameterDefinition
desc: A time period defined by a start and end date and optionally time.

name: $Period
desc: A measured amount (or an amount that can potentially be measured). Note that measured amounts include amounts that are not precisely quantified, including amounts involving arbitrary units and floating currencies.

name: $Quantity
desc: A set of ordered Quantities defined by a low and high limit.

name: $Range
desc: A relationship of two Quantity values - expressed as a numerator and a denominator.

name: $Ratio
desc: A reference from one resource to another.

name: $Reference
desc: Related artifacts such as additional documentation, justification, or bibliographic references.

name: $RelatedArtifact
desc: A series of measurements taken by a device, with upper and lower limits. There may be more than one dimension in the data.

name: $SampledData
desc: A digital signature along with supporting context. The signature may be electronic/cryptographic in nature, or a graphical image representing a hand-written signature, or a signature process. Different signature approaches have different utilities.

name: $SimpleQuantity
desc: Specifies an event that may occur multiple times. Timing schedules are used to record when things are planned, expected or requested to occur. The most common usage is in dosage instructions for medications. They are also used when planning care of various kinds, and may be used for reporting the schedule to which past regular activities were carried out.

name: $Timing
desc: A description of a triggering event.

name: $TriggerDefinition
desc: Specifies clinical/business/etc metadata that can be used to retrieve, index and/or categorize an artifact. This metadata can either be specific to the applicable population (e.g., age category, DRG) or the specific context of care (e.g., venue, care setting, provider of care).

name: $UsageContext
desc: A stream of bytes

name: $base64Binary
desc: Value of "true" or "false"

name: $boolean
desc: A string which has at least one character and no leading or trailing whitespace and where there is no whitespace other than single spaces in the contents

name: $code
desc: A date or partial date (e.g. just year or year + month). There is no time zone. The format is a union of the schema types gYear, gYearMonth and date.  Dates SHALL be valid dates.

name: $date
desc: A date, date-time or partial date (e.g. just year or year + month).  If hours and minutes are specified, a time zone SHALL be populated. The format is a union of the schema types gYear, gYearMonth, date and dateTime. Seconds must be provided due to schema type constraints but may be zero-filled and may be ignored.                 Dates SHALL be valid dates.

name: $dateTime
desc: A rational number with implicit precision

name: $decimal
desc: Any combination of letters, numerals, "-" and ".", with a length limit of 64 characters.  (This might be an integer, an unprefixed OID, UUID or any other identifier pattern that meets these constraints.)  Ids are case-insensitive.

name: $id
desc: An instant in time - known at least to the second

name: $instant
desc: A whole number

name: $integer
desc: A string that may contain markdown syntax for optional processing by a mark down presentation engine

name: $markdown
desc: An OID represented as a URI

name: $oid
desc: An integer with a value that is positive (e.g. >0)

name: $positiveInt
desc: A sequence of Unicode characters

name: $string
desc: A time during the day, with no date specified

name: $time
desc: An integer with a value that is not negative (e.g. >= 0)

name: $unsignedInt
desc: String of characters used to identify a name or a resource

name: $uri
desc: A UUID, represented as a URI

name: $uuid
desc: XHTML format, as defined by W3C, but restricted usage (mainly, no active content)
